Marketing. Marketing management. Specifics of product marketing and service marketing. Creating and developing a service culture based on a customer-centric mindset. Well-known methods for controlling, measuring and evaluating the quality of services. 
Product and service and their price in marketing. Promotional and public relations marketing. Marketing strategies. Sales process and its organization. Sales techniques at different sales stages, sales negotiations. 
Sales. Sales management. Customer relations. Sales strategies and sales planning.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to understand the basic principles and nature of marketing and sales management in order to understand their interrelationships and role in organizational sustainability.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) know the nature of the basic concepts of marketing and sales management and their interrelation; 2) know the basic concepts of service development and marketing; 3) know the connections of marketing and sales management with other areas of a company's activities; 4) know the nature of the sales process and the main sales techniques; 5) be able to plan and analyze a company's marketing processes; 6) be able to highlight the role of marketing in the successful operation and development of a company; 7) be able to implement various representation activities; 8) be able to organize a company's sales activities.
